5:
Heed me, stars! Unravel what stands
before us!
34: No... This can't be real! IT CAN'T!
49:
Hey! You know something, don't
you?! Are you telling me THAT'S the
dragon?!
55: N-no... I was... I was just told to...
59: But... who? Who... told me to?
75:
LET ME GO! I've got to get Hoshi out
of there!
85:
That thing is already dead. It's over.
It's been over for a long, long time...
99:
But it was also the beginning of
everything...
102:
A city, erased at the end of time.
From the empty space, a dragon
emerged, rending the world. The
dragon did battle with humans...
105:
And the humans were the victors.
But, within the dragon's body, they
found something.
114:
It was a corpse—a godlike being, but
in the form of a child.
116:
They tried to duplicate them both.
The dragon and the boy. And from
those corpses, they birthed puppets.
119: That was how I came to be.
124:
Whatever sick joke this is, Nova... you
need to stop it right now!
131:
This is what happens when things
get mixed together. I'm sure you can
understand... Ayumu Nagihara.
141:
The god, who dared wish for both
death and happiness. The Overlords,
who desired an endless dream...
144: Now, I will set things right.
151:
Together, with those of us who
should never have been born...
166: I no longer answer to that name...
172:
I am nothing more than a husk—I
am Remna.
225: The first Stella was a failure.
230:
It failed much in the same way as
the god who desired to end it all. It
was incomplete... It gained a soul.
233:
Never did I expect the Goddess of
the Stars to malfunction in the same
way. You were meant to be
immune—a miscalculation, to be
sure.
243:
No matter. I shall deal with these
errors myself.
248:
Stella... Leve... Get out of here while
you can!
253:
Stella... For all our sakes, you must
join with me!
